yields:

@media screen and (min-width:461px) {
  background: url("image_740.jpg");
}
@media screen and (max-width:460px) {
  h1.title {
    background: url("image_460.jpg");
  }
}

In the first media-query block the outer scope h1.title was lost by lesscpy

It really should be:

@media screen and (max-width: 460px) {
  h1.title {
    background: url("image_460.jpg");
  }
}
@media screen and (min-width: 461px) {
  h1.title {
    background: url("image_740.jpg");
  }
}

Currently snapshot cronjobs get --timestring added. This results in curator giving a warning that --timestring is used, but neither --newer-than nor --older-than is used. This prevents the command from actually executing through cron. This simple patch fixes that:

--- a/modules/curator/manifests/job.pp
+++ b/modules/curator/manifests/job.pp
@@ -81,7 +81,11 @@ define curator::job (
     $_regex = undef
   }

-  $_timestring = "--timestring '${timestring}'"
+  if ($command == "snapshot") {
+    $_timestring = undef
+  else {
+    $_timestring = "--timestring '${timestring}'"
+  }

